<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07830</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT INCREASING THE YEARLY ALLOCATION FOR SCIENTIFIC AND TECHNOLOGICAL ACTIVITIES (STA) AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to allocate 1% of Gross Domestic Product (GDP) as annual budget for science and technology activities (STA) for generation, advancement, dissemination, and application of scientific knowledge in all fields of Science and Technology; Creates a special fund for research and development to be known as “R&D” from the following sources: a. allocation of 1 percent (1%) of GDP for S&T activities; b. all unused R&D allocation; and c. all income derived from R&D activities</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-05-31</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON SCIENCE AND TECHNOLOGY ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>